HEADWORD: glitch
<hw>glitch</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A fault or defect in a
system, plan, or machine.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> bug.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Elect.)</fld> <def>A brief surge or interruption in
the voltage in an electrical circuit or device.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

